text.tspan: Basically any size can be used for the tunnel.
The hole in the dome is cut after welding the entire dome.
The following template can be used for bending
sheet material to match the rendered oven.
It is intended for 2 cm insulation between the sheets.
The dimensions below are guidelines, use some extra material.
Use completed domes as template for bottom sheets.
The inner and outer sheets should have a 5 cm space between.
By default the inner dome has a diameter of 60 cm.
Adjust this diameter to another value by scaling the print of pages 2-10
Scale factor = Desired diameter in cetimeters / 60
Verify this by measuring the length of this ruler where the length
of the ruler in mm corresponds to the dome diameter in cm.
Your printer settings may need fine adjustment to get the "100%",
(for example I had to print at 105% to get the correct ruler length).
By default the outer dome has a diameter of 70 cm.
This leaves a space of 5m for insulation between the domes.
Adjust this diameter to another value by scaling the print of pages 11-21
Scale factor = Desired diameter in cetimeters / 70
Verify this by measuring the length of the ruler where the length
of the ruler in mm corresponds to the dome diameter in cm.
Inner diameter of 60 cm with 10 cm insulation
Print 60 cm inner (100%) and 80 cm outer (114.3%)
Inner diameter of 80 cm with 5 cm insulation
Print 80 cm inner (133.3%) and 90 cm outer (128.6%)
